author: CNN
description: The Supreme Court on Thursday allowed Texas to use a congressional map that will boost President Donald Trump’s effort to keep Republicans in control of Congress, blocking a lower court decision that found the new boundaries were likely unconstitutional because they were drawn based on race. #CNN #News
title: Supreme Court allows Texas to use Trump-backed congressional maps for midterms

author: CNN
description: A grand jury declined to indict New York Attorney General Letitia James after being asked to look at the mortgage fraud case against her a second time, 10 days after a federal judge threw out the initial charges against her, according to a person familiar with the development Thursday. #CNN #News
title: Grand Jury declines to re-indict NY AG Letitia James

author: CNN
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin declared Russia will take the Donbas region “by military or other means,” as Ukraine enters more deadlocked peace talks. He arrived in New Delhi for talks with Indian Prime Minister Narendra ]Modi, days after meeting a U.S. delegation in Moscow.                                                  #CNN #News
title: Putin vows to seize Donbas “by any means,” as Ukraine prepares for new U.S.-backed peace talks

author: CNN
description: Vaccine advisers to the CDC could vote soon on dramatic changes to hepatitis B vaccination practice in the United States. CNN's Dr. Sanjay Gupta explains the impact hepatitis B vaccines have had on public health and some of the dangers if the recommendations are changed.
title: Dr. Gupta explains impact of Hepatitis B vaccines

author: CNN
description: Citing organizers’ decision to admit Israel, Spain, Ireland, Slovenia and the Netherlands declared Thursday they will not take part in next year’s Eurovision Song Contest.                                             #CNN #News
title: Four European nations boycott Eurovision over Israel’s inclusion

author: CNN
description:
A New Orleans City Council meeting went into recess this morning after protests erupted when public comment was suspended. CNN reached out to police for comment, who said there were no injuries and no arrests made.

#cnn #news #immigration #neworleans #louisiana
title: Protesters removed from New Orleans City Council meeting

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump’s name was added to the US Institute of Peace (USIP) building. CNN’s Kylie Atwood explains why it has created controversy.
title: Trump’s name added to US Institute of Peace building

author: CNN
description: Mohamed Amin Ahmed, a Somali immigrant and Republican for 25 years told CNN he campaigned and voted for President Donald Trump in 2024. After Trump’s recent comments calling the community “garbage” Ahmed speaks to CNN’s Whitney Wild. #cnn #news #politics
title: This Somali immigrant voted for Trump. Hear his message to him

author: CNN
description: Attorney General Pam Bondi announced that Brian Cole Jr., the man accused of planting viable pipe bombs outside the DNC and RNC offices the night before the 2021 attack, has been federally charged with using an explosive device.
title: Bondi touts DOJ solving pipe bomber case

author: CNN
description: Age is just a number: How Emma Mazzenga is redefining athletic longevity at 92 years old and scientist are trying to figure out how she’s doing it.
title: Italian scientists are studying her to learn about aging

author: CNN
description:
Cyclone Senyar brought deadly flooding and landslides to parts of Indonesia.
#cnn #news
title: House collapses, road crumbles in Indonesia flooding

author: CNN
description: The top Democrat on the House Intelligence Committee said leaving a briefing with top US military officials that what he learned about September’s double-tap strike in the Caribbean was “one of the most troubling things” he’s seen as a congressman. Rep. Jim Himes of Connecticut told reporters that Admiral Frank “Mitch” Bradley defended the decisions taken during the September strike. CNN’s Brianna Keilar speaks with Rep. Don Bacon (R-NE) to get his reaction.                                                                                                 #CNN #News
title: ‘One of the most troubling things I’ve seen’: Lawmakers briefed on double-tap strike

author: CNN
description: A lost baby fur seal waddled into a craft beer bar in Richmond, New Zealand, prompting bartenders to lure the unaccompanied minor to safety with a treat. #cnn #news #animals
title: Baby seal wanders into a bar

author: CNN
description: The artist known as Beeple has caused a stir at Art Basel in Miami with an eye-catching new installation. Titled "Regular Animals," the piece sees Elon Musk, Mark Zuckerberg and Andy Warhol, among others, reimagined as robot dogs that poop pictures. #CNN #News
title: See robotic dogs with human heads causing a scene at Miami art fair

author: CNN
description: The CNN Creators have had a busy week meeting Anna Wintour, Arsène Wenger and Formula 1 drivers in the Qatar Grand Prix paddock. They also discuss the controversy surrounding the announcement of the Bezos' as lead sponsors of Met Gala 2026 as well as the rise of water sommeliers and menus at a handful of luxury restaurants. #CNN #News
title: CNN CREATORS: Met Gala drama, water sommeliers and Formula 1

author: CNN
description: CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten breaks down public sentiment on the US labor market as President Donald Trump’s first year back in office nears its end.  #CNN #News
title: ‘It’s rough out there’: Enten runs number on US job market

author: CNN
description: Australian content creator Samuel Weidenhofer traveled to Detroit to meet Ed Bambas, an 88-year-old veteran working at a Meijer grocery store. Weidenhofer then started a GoFundMe to help try to retire Ed, which has raised over $1.5 million.
title: Content creator tries to retire 88-year-old veteran

author: CNN
description: A synagogue in Los Angeles was vandalized by pro-Palestinian protestors on Wednesday during a community safety meeting. According to the Los Angeles Police Department, two people were arrested but their names have not yet been released. #cnn #lasynagogue #losangeles
title: Synagogue vandalized during protest

author: CNN
description: The FBI arrested a man from Woodbridge, Virginia, on Thursday who investigators believe planted pipe bombs near the Republican and Democratic National Committee headquarters the night before the 2021 US Capitol riot, according to two law enforcement sources. Multiple law enforcement officials have identified the man as Brian Cole Jr. CNN has observed local and federal law enforcement outside his known residence in the Washington, DC, suburb. #CNN #News
title: Law enforcement sources name suspect in DC Pipe Bomb case

author: CNN
description: The Trump administration has made immigration court a focal point of its deportation strategy. A former immigration judge breaks down the strategies used by the Department of Homeland Security to hasten the removal of asylum seekers, including firing immigration judges nationwide.
title: Trump administration purges more immigration judges

author: CNN
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin said Moscow would seize Ukraine’s Donbas region “by military or other means,” digging in on one of his key demands as Ukrainian officials prepare for more peace talks that have yet to yield a deal. Putin arrived in New Delhi on Thursday where he will be hosted by Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi, two days after a meeting at the Kremlin with a US delegation led by special envoy Steve Witkoff.  #CNN #News
title: Putin vows Russia will seize Donbas region by any means

author: CNN
description: The FBI arrested a man who investigators believe planted pipe bombs near the Republican and Democratic National Committee headquarters the night before the 2021 US Capitol riot, according to two law enforcement sources. CNN Senior Justice Correspondent Evan Perez reports.
title: FBI makes arrest in DC pipe bomber investigation

author: CNN
description: The family of a Colombian man believed to have been killed in a US strike in the Caribbean has filed what’s believed to be the first complaint against such attacks with the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights (IACHR). The petition, filed by US human rights attorney Dan Kovalik, alleges that Colombian fisherman Alejandro Carranza was killed when the US struck his boat off the coast of Colombia on September 15.  #CNN #News
title: Family files first known complaint over deadly boat strike

author: CNN
description: Pop star Sabrina Carpenter has slammed the White House for posting a video depicting law enforcement apprehending individuals in apparent immigration actions to her song "Juno." Responding to the tweet on X she called the video "evil and disgusting." #CNN
title: Sabrina Carpenter calls White House video using her song ‘evil and disgusting’

author: CNN
description: CarolAnn Tutera, a victim of David Gentile — the CEO sentenced to seven years for a fraud scheme — says she is disgusted that Trump pardoned him. CNN’s Jake Tapper reports. #CNN #news
title: 'Disgusted': Victim reacts to Trump pardoning CEO convicted of fraud

author: CNN
description: CNN's Bijan Hosseini sat down with F1 driver Isack Hadjar, days before it was announced that he'll be racing for Red Bull in 2026, joining four-time Formula 1 champion Max Verstappen. The French-Algerian has had an impressive season as a rookie with Racing Bulls, Red Bull's junior team.
title: Newly-promoted Red Bull driver Isack Hadjar speaks to CNN

author: CNN
description: The Team USA uniforms just dropped. Ralph Lauren has been dressing Olympic athletes on Team USA for nearly 20 years. They just unveiled the new look for 2026, including jackets, boots, mittens, and belts, all made in the USA.
title: Ralph Lauren unveils Team USA uniforms

author: CNN
description: The FBI arrested a man on Thursday who investigators believe planted pipe bombs near the Republican and Democratic National Committee headquarters the night before the 2021 US Capitol riot, according to two law enforcement sources. The arrest follows an almost five-year investigation to uncover the identity of the bomber who has only been seen in grainy surveillance video shrouded in a hoodie, gloves and a face mask. CNN's Evan Perez reports. #CNN #News
title: FBI makes arrest in Jan. 6 DC pipe bomber investigation, sources say

author: CNN
description: In the run-up to the 2026 FIFA World Cup draw, CNN’s Amanda Davies looks at some of the old and new soccer stars aiming to leave their mark on the tournament. #cnn #news
title: Who is set to play in next year's World Cup?

author: CNN
description: The Trump administration is targeting undocumented Somali immigrants during immigration enforcement operations in Minnesota. Minneapolis Police Chief Brian O'Hara explains why his department will not help ICE with the operations. #cnn #news #minneapolis
title: Minneapolis Police Chief explains why he won't help ICE

author: CNN
description: A new watchdog report found that Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth risked compromising sensitive military information, which could have endangered US troops and mission objectives, when he used Signal to share highly-sensitive attack plans in Yemen, according four sources familiar with the contents of a classified assessment. Hegseth claimed this report exonerated him, but Republican Senator Thom Tillis sharply disagreed. #CNN #News
title: GOP senator says Hegseth was not exonerated by new watchdog report

author: CNN
description: The family of a man whose moment of anguish during the deadly Hong Kong apartment fire was captured in a viral photo, says they are reeling as the man’s wife remains missing. #cnn #news
title: What's the story behind this Hong Kong fire photo?

author: CNN
description: As lawmakers demand answers over reports that the US military carried out a follow-up strike that killed survivors during an attacked on an alleged drug boat in the Caribbean, a career Navy SEAL who has spent most of his 30 years of military experience in special operations will be responsible for providing them. Adm. Frank “Mitch” Bradley, who now leads US Special Operations Command, heads to Capitol Hill to brief members of Congress on what happened as part of that September 2 strike as well as the way the military is carrying out its campaign that has destroyed more than 20 boats and killed 83.  #CNN #News
title: Admiral under scrutiny for double-tap boat strike set to brief lawmakers

author: CNN
description: CNN Tech reporter Clare Duffy walks through the settings on Instagram, Snapchat, and TikTok that exist to help parents monitor their child's social media use. For more on this, check out her podcast "Terms of Service." #cnn #cnnnews
title: Have a child on social media? Here is how to monitor what they are up to

author: CNN
description:
Audie talks with CNN’s Donie O’Sullivan about how people are reshaping their spiritual lives -- from Wicca to aliens -- and searching for new sources of meaning. Donie is exploring all of this in a new docu-series called “Devoted.” It’s available on CNN All Access.

Listen to the full episode of CNN's The Assignment podcast: http://swap.fm/l/tawacyt120425

#cnn #news #spirituality #religion #aliens #wicca #witches #audiecornish #cnnallaccess
title: America isn’t done with God... or witches, or aliens | The Assignment

author: CNN
description: Quarterback Fernando Mendoza is making history at Indiana University with a perfect season. He also has a real shot at the Heisman trophy. CNN’s Brynn Gingras travels to his old High School in Miami to learn what makes this player so special. Stream the full story on the CNN app.
title: Undefeated ‘football nerd’ gives Indiana hope

author: CNN
description: The family of a man whose moment of anguish during the deadly Hong Kong apartment fire was captured in a viral photo, says they are reeling as the man’s wife remains missing. #cnn #news
title: What’s the story behind this Hong Kong fire photo?

author: CNN
description: Musician Nick Cave has experienced the death of two of his sons. He tells CNN's Anderson Cooper why his experience with grief has made him feel more human. Watch the full episode and join the conversation at cnn.com/allthereis #cnn #nickcave
title: Musician Nick Cave says grief made him 'more fully human'

author: CNN
description: Kiyoshi Fujimoto, chef of Japanese restaurant Les KaneKIYOs, speaks with CNN about how he started specializing in bear meat cuisine. Japan has seen a record number of fatal bear attacks in 2025. The government has recently deployed security forces to deal with the issue. #cnn #news #bear #japan
title: Bear is on the menu at this Japanese restaurant

author: CNN
description: Video shows Palestinians rushing to extinguish flames that erupted in tents after an Israeli missile hit a displacement camp in Khan Younis, Gaza, killing at least five and injuring dozens according to Civil Defense spokesman Mahmoud Bassal and a nearby hospital. The Israeli military said it was targeting Hamas members, alleging the militant group violated the ceasefire agreement injuring five soldiers. #cnn #news
title: Palestinians frantically pour water on a blaze caused by an Israeli strike

author: CNN
description: A rare species of palm tree blooms once in its lifetime in Rio de Janeiro and then dies. Brazil’s Botanical Garden is working to preserve its life cycle. #cnn #news #brazil #palmtree
title: Rare palm trees bloom once in a lifetime before dying in Rio

author: CNN
description: We’re days from learning how the FIFA World Cup may unfold, with the final draw taking place Friday in Washington, D.C.—a first. Forty-eight teams will be placed into 12 groups of four, and on Saturday FIFA will release the full match schedule. Canada has automatically qualified as a co-host alongside the U.S. and Mexico. CNN’s Paula Newton speaks with two major figures in Canadian soccer: Diego Moratorio, GM of MLS Canada, and Peter Montopoli, Canada’s Chief Tourna             #CNN #News
title: Fans await Friday’s reveal in FIFA World Cup draw

author: CNN
description:
Video taken in Kenner, Louisiana shows two men standing on a roof Wednesday as federal agents surround a home in a suburb outside of New Orleans. It’s not clear why Border Patrol agents did not attempt to get the two men off the roof before leaving the scene or if the men are undocumented.

#cnn #news #immigration #trump #usa #louisiana
title: Two men appear to wait out Border Patrol agents on roof

author: CNN
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un attended the 80th anniversary of the Korean People’s Army Air Force, accompanied by his daughter believed to be Kim Ju Ae, an appearance that adds to her growing number of widely publicized outings. #cnn #news
title: North Korean leader and his daughter attend 80th Air Force anniversary

author: CNN
description: After President Trump's inflammatory rhetoric against Somalis and Minnesota Democratic Rep. Ilhan Omar, the congresswoman told CNN's Jake Tapper she is not surprised by the president's words, saying he is "trying to "scapegoat and deflect."
title: Rep. Ilhan Omar hits back on Trump comments: ‘We are Americans’

author: CNN
description: Photos and videos from Jeffrey Epstein’s former Caribbean island were released by House Democrats on the Oversight Committee, shedding fresh light on the site of his decades-long abuse.                 #CNN #News
title: House Democrats release photos and video from Epstein’s private island

author: CNN
description: A Thunderbird pilot had to eject from a F-16C Fighting Falcon jet that crashed during a training mission near Trona, California. It’s unclear what caused the crash. The Air Force said the incident is under investigation.
title: Thunderbird pilot ejects from F-16C jet

author: CNN
description: Business and life strategist Tony Robbins shares with Elex Michaelson a personal story of hope during the holiday season.
title: ‘Help them’: Tony Robbins shares a message of hope

author: CNN
description: Pete Hegseth endangered U.S. troops by sharing sensitive war plans, according to a highly damning Pentagon inspector general report. The investigation found he posted the plans in a group chat that included journalist Jeffrey Goldberg—an extraordinary rebuke of a sitting defense secretary. The report lands as questions grow over Hegseth’s leadership after a second strike on an alleged drug boat killed two survivors. President Trump is now pledging to release video of that strike.                                 #CNN #News
title: Pentagon report concludes Hegseth risked endangering troops

author: CNN
description: CNN's Stefano Pozzebon was at Simon Bolivar Intl Airport in Venezuela when US deportation flights landed, despite President Trump declaring the country’s airspace should be considered closed.
title: CNN is at airport in Venezuela as US deportation flights land

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said on Wednesday that he would release the video of the second strike on the alleged drug vessel off the coast of Venezuela. Rhode Island Democratic Senator Jack Reed tells CNN's Kasie Hunt that lawmakers have yet to see the video.
title: Will Trump release video of second strike on alleged drug boat?

author: CNN
description: Despite having no official role in the Trump administration in his second term, President Donald Trump’s son-in-law, Jared Kushner, played a key role in ceasefire talks between Israel and Hamas and is now at the center of negotiations between Ukraine and Russia. CNN’s Alayna Treene explains his role in these talks.
title: Jared Kushner’s unconventional role in peace negotiations
